query: Who among the listed marshals also held the post of Supreme Commander of the Royal Thai Armed Forces Headquarters and during which periods were they Prime Ministers of Thailand?
summary: Among the listed marshals who also held the post of Supreme Commander of the Royal Thai Armed Forces Headquarters are Plaek Phibunsongkhram, Sarit Thanarat, and Thanom Kittikachorn. Plaek Phibunsongkhram served as the Prime Minister of Thailand from 1938 to 1944 and again from 1948 to 1957. query: Over the years, which engine has been used frequently by Ed Carpenter in the Indianapolis 500 and did this choice of engine coincide with his best finish positions?
